conditions.condition:
2nd Implementation Period: CP 1. Prior to the disbursement by the Global Fund to the Principal Recipient of Grant funds to finance the procurement of second-line anti-tuberculosis drugs, the Principal Recipient shall make available to the Global Fund, in form and substance satisfactory to the Global Fund, the following:

a.	An updated detailed multi-drug resistant tuberculosis ("MDR-TB") expansion plan, developed in collaboration with a technical partner that includes: 

i.	the number of MDR-TB patients to be treated, which shall be consistent and manageable with the expansion plan on treatment sites/ number of beds; 
ii.	the list and quantifications of the medicines to be procured for the MDR-TB program, which shall reflect the Principal Recipient’s finalized forecast for the Implementation Period covered by the Grant Agreement;
iii.	an expansion plan for programmatic management of drug-resistant TB which is consistent with the WHO guidelines (i.e. a system that primarily employs ambulatory models of care to manage patients with drug-resistant TB); and 
iv.	the resource contributions of the Government, Global Fund and other partners for the 2013-2015 period;

b.	National guidelines for the programmatic management of MDR-TB, also developed in collaboration with a technical partner acceptable to the Global Fund; and

c.	For each disbursement request that includes funds for the procurement of MDR-TB medicines, a pro forma invoice issued by the designated Procurement Agent of the Global Drug Facility, as delegated by the Green Light Committee Initiative.

The delivery of a completed version of the Monitoring and Evaluation Systems Strengthening Tool prepared by the Principal Recipient in consultation with the Program stakeholders;
b. The delivery of an updated plan for monitoring and evaluating Program activities (the "Updated M&E Plan") that incorporates the recommendations made by Program stakeholders upon completion of the Monitoring and Evaluation Systems Strengthening Tool;
c. The delivery of a revised budget for the Program Term (the "Revised Program Budget") if the amendments incorporated into the Updated M&E Plan necessitate amendments to the budget for the Program Term that was approved by the Global Fund as of the effective date of this Agreement; and
d. The written approval of the Global Fund of the Updated M&E Plan and Revised Program Budget.

IP 1: The delivery by the Principal Recipient to the Global Fund of an updated Comprehensive Manual of Procedures (the "Manual"), in form and substance satisfactory to the Global Fund, containing, without limitation, procedures to ensure that adequate mechanisms are in place for the proper segregation of duties and internal controls at the Principal Recipient’s Program Management Unit. The Manual shall include complete details of the Principal Recipient’s policies  and any other relevant policies relating to the management of Grant funds, such as the following:

i.	accounting and financial procedures (including inventory, asset management and cash management which includes petty cash ceilings);
ii.	human resources policies and procedures (including updated organogram and approved salary scale); 
iii.	procurement policy and procedures; 
iv.	policy on conflict of interest of the Principal Recipient; and 
v.	policies and procedures for the management of Sub-recipients, including disbursements to and expenditure monitoring of Sub-recipients.

IP 1: The delivery by the Principal Recipient of evidence, in form and substance satisfactory to the Global Fund,  establishing that the Principal Recipient has complied with the following:

i.	the installation and use of an accounting software package, which includes: (i) a budget management and tracking tool enabling timely cash reconciliation; and (ii) a reporting tool enabling monthly management reports;
ii.	the revision of the Terms of Reference of the Fiduciary Agent to incorporate a plan for the strengthening of the technical capacities of the Principal Recipient’s Finance and Administrative staff;
iii.	the recruitment of an appropriately qualified and experienced Accounting Officer; and
iv.	the appointment of an appropriately qualified and experienced external auditor for a maximum non-renewable term of 2 years.

IP 1: The use of Grant funds by the Principal Recipient to finance the activities of a Sub-recipient is subject to the satisfaction of each of the following conditions:

1.	 the delivery by the Principal Recipient to the Global Fund, in form and substance satisfactory to the Global Fund, of an updated Sub-recipient Manual of Procedures (the "SR Manual") that includes, without limitation, the following items which are applicable to the management of all Sub-recipients:

i.	procedures for the selection, assessment and confirmation of Sub-recipients and negotiation of Sub-recipient agreements;
ii.	procedures for the identification of gaps and/or weaknesses in Sub-recipients’ capacity and provision of  relevant mitigating measures; 
iii.	ongoing monitoring and supervision of Sub-recipients’ performance and provision of capacity-building activities; 
iv.	performance of  programmatic and financial management oversight of Sub-recipients, including the review of reporting timelines and performance frameworks of  all Sub-recipients and quality program aspects including quality of services provided to beneficiaries, cash and inventory management;
v.		procedures for processing disbursement requests from Sub-recipients in an efficient and transparent manner; and
vi.		accounting, financial, and internal control procedures at the Principal Recipient and the relevant Sub-recipient level ensuring that adequate mechanisms are in place at the Principal Recipient and the relevant Sub-recipient level for proper segregation of duties in the disbursement to, and oversight process of, Sub-recipients (including sub-sub-recipients) and their staff; and  

2. the delivery by the Principal Recipient to the Global Fund, prior to the signing of any agreement with the Sub-recipients of a detailed workplan and budget for each Sub-recipient, in form and substance satisfactory to the Global Fund.
